1
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:25,700
"The Edge of Horizon"
(Episode 1)

2
00:01:34,777 --> 00:01:35,778
[1902]

3
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,857
Thank you, Phob.

4
00:01:59,301 --> 00:02:00,657
(In unison) Let's go.

5
00:02:01,724 --> 00:02:02,970
Go straight.

6
00:02:06,697 --> 00:02:07,937
[1914]

7
00:02:08,537 --> 00:02:11,977
Definite rules for
spacing are not successful,

8
00:02:12,737 --> 00:02:15,377
it is a matter of a draftsman's judgement

9
00:02:15,687 --> 00:02:17,217
and sense of design.

10
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:32,817
I'd like to present cotton
rose to you, Your Highness.

11
00:02:35,495 --> 00:02:36,496
Sure, you can.

12
00:02:40,297 --> 00:02:41,617
I should tuck it behind your ear.

13
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:43,377
- No!
- Why not?

14
00:02:43,559 --> 00:02:44,879
It doesn't suit me, it suits you.

15
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:47,457
It looks better on you.

16
00:02:47,852 --> 00:02:49,497
Come on.

17
00:02:51,719 --> 00:02:52,897
So adorable.

18
00:02:53,596 --> 00:02:55,977
- I don't think so.
- Of course, it is.

19
00:02:57,287 --> 00:03:00,337
Stop touching it already. Stop, okay?

20
00:03:00,817 --> 00:03:03,777
Stop fidgeting already.
Stay still like this.

21
00:03:04,777 --> 00:03:07,217
- I can't take it out?
- No, you can't. Just keep it like that.

22
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:09,737
[Varakulvatin Palace]

23
00:03:26,329 --> 00:03:27,937
Hey! All of you!

24
00:03:28,399 --> 00:03:30,577
Stop running around like monkeys!

25
00:03:30,964 --> 00:03:34,177
He will have gifts for eveyone.

26
00:03:36,495 --> 00:03:38,577
Euam, well…

27
00:03:38,665 --> 00:03:41,057
why are they giving us gifts?

28
00:03:41,337 --> 00:03:42,977
It's not even Songkran.

29
00:03:43,497 --> 00:03:46,297
Well, Prince Vasin just got promoted

30
00:03:47,697 --> 00:03:51,457
so they're kind enough
to give something to us.

31
00:03:52,817 --> 00:03:54,977
We're so lucky

32
00:03:54,987 --> 00:03:56,777
to have kind masters like them.

33
00:03:57,836 --> 00:04:00,037
Sathu.

34
00:04:00,377 --> 00:04:02,537
What are you waiting for? Come on.

35
00:04:17,097 --> 00:04:18,377
Thank you, Your Highness.

36
00:04:19,897 --> 00:04:23,977
Nual, where is your son?

37
00:04:24,409 --> 00:04:25,977
Call him for me.

38
00:04:26,377 --> 00:04:27,857
I have something for him.

39
00:04:29,545 --> 00:04:32,577
Phob is hanging out with
Prince Tinnakorn for sure.

40
00:04:32,873 --> 00:04:36,457
When you see Prince Tinnakorn,
you will see Phob there.

41
00:04:37,188 --> 00:04:41,057
Just like me, waiting to
serve you, Your Highness.

42
00:04:41,188 --> 00:04:42,189
Stop it.

43
00:04:45,103 --> 00:04:47,057
Why don't you call him for me?

44
00:04:47,817 --> 00:04:48,818
Yes, Your Highness.

45
00:05:00,799 --> 00:05:02,537
- Watch out!
- I'm okay.

46
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,665
Please be careful, Your Highness.

47
00:05:06,543 --> 00:05:08,217
I think I should get it for you.

48
00:05:08,569 --> 00:05:10,169
Why are you yelling?

49
00:05:10,495 --> 00:05:13,537
Be careful. There are many flowers,

50
00:05:13,945 --> 00:05:15,617
why do you want that one?

51
00:05:15,865 --> 00:05:17,766
I like this one.

52
00:05:18,623 --> 00:05:19,624
Watch out!

53
00:05:30,321 --> 00:05:31,322
Phob!

54
00:05:35,993 --> 00:05:38,377
Stay still, I will clean it for you.

55
00:05:50,348 --> 00:05:51,349
Can you wipe it off?

56
00:05:52,737 --> 00:05:53,738
Sure, I can.

57
00:05:59,639 --> 00:06:01,577
I was so worried about you

58
00:06:02,108 --> 00:06:03,617
and you made fun of my face.

59
00:06:04,423 --> 00:06:05,424
You're so mean.

60
00:06:06,105 --> 00:06:08,257
You looked funny when you fell.

61
00:06:11,057 --> 00:06:12,697
Stop sulking already.

62
00:06:14,137 --> 00:06:15,138
Smile.

63
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,057
Smile.

64
00:06:22,159 --> 00:06:23,439
Stop making a grumpy face already.

65
00:06:27,151 --> 00:06:29,017
Smile, come on. Wider.

66
00:06:30,121 --> 00:06:32,657
- You still got some dirt on you.
- Phob.

67
00:06:37,143 --> 00:06:38,577
The Princess is calling for you.

68
00:06:40,144 --> 00:06:41,145
Okay, Mom.

69
00:06:51,305 --> 00:06:53,137
I met Khun Luang Prat yesterday.

70
00:06:53,593 --> 00:06:55,857
Your teacher said that
you're a bright student.

71
00:06:56,263 --> 00:06:59,017
You're a fast learner.
You've done so well in school.

72
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:07,057
Thank you, Your Highness,

73
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:10,257
for allowing my son to study.

74
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:22,537
Your son is a bright student.

75
00:07:23,017 --> 00:07:25,828
My son and I talked

76
00:07:25,887 --> 00:07:29,377
and we decided to pay for his
tuition fee as long as he wants.

77
00:07:29,599 --> 00:07:33,297
We wish that he won't
have to serve us in the future.

78
00:07:34,937 --> 00:07:37,057
Instead, he should serve the nation.

79
00:07:45,716 --> 00:07:46,777
Thank you, Your Highness.

80
00:07:48,097 --> 00:07:50,548
Phob is doing so well in
school, Dad and Grandma.

81
00:07:50,836 --> 00:07:54,217
He always helped me with the lessons.

82
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:57,937
No matter how good
he is, he still is a servant.

83
00:07:58,497 --> 00:08:01,137
He was born in a lower class of society
so he still needs to crawl.

84
00:08:03,257 --> 00:08:05,857
You can give him more pens
but you can't change his servant blood.

85
00:08:06,377 --> 00:08:07,657
Tin, you should know about this.

86
00:08:07,865 --> 00:08:09,785
Don't praise him too
much or he would get cocky.

87
00:08:10,104 --> 00:08:11,697
I'm just telling the truth.

88
00:08:12,273 --> 00:08:14,217
Actually, you should let him

89
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,537
tutor you sometimes

90
00:08:16,628 --> 00:08:18,629
- so you'd do better in school.
- Tin!

91
00:08:18,637 --> 00:08:21,117
If you don't have nice things to say,
then keep your mouth shut.

92
00:08:21,923 --> 00:08:25,083
You're doing nothing but getting off track.

93
00:08:25,358 --> 00:08:27,137
You're bringing shame to the family.

94
00:08:28,305 --> 00:08:30,497
You won't study, you don't
care about reading books.

95
00:08:30,908 --> 00:08:32,257
Since you were young until now,

96
00:08:32,335 --> 00:08:34,657
can you be as good as the servant's son?

97
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:47,834
Phob,

98
00:08:48,492 --> 00:08:50,497
don't mind Chat.

99
00:08:50,556 --> 00:08:52,257
But what he said was true.

100
00:08:52,557 --> 00:08:54,137
Who cares if I'm doing great in school?

101
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:57,257
I can only be a servant,

102
00:08:58,348 --> 00:08:59,508
a lower class of society.

103
00:08:59,884 --> 00:09:00,885
Phob,

104
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,261
look at this.

105
00:09:22,175 --> 00:09:23,177
Cotton rose

106
00:09:24,991 --> 00:09:26,577
is white in the morning,

107
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:29,137
then it changes to pink at noon.

108
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:33,777
And in the evening, it
won't be the same anymore.

109
00:09:36,552 --> 00:09:39,857
In the future, your status can be different
based on your potential.

110
00:09:41,777 --> 00:09:43,217
Nothing can stop you.

111
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:47,977
You're determined and focused.

112
00:09:48,857 --> 00:09:50,177
I believe in you.

113
00:09:58,391 --> 00:09:59,457
Thank you, Your Highness.

114
00:10:03,071 --> 00:10:04,180
You've been so good to me

115
00:10:06,004 --> 00:10:07,457
since we were young.

116
00:10:08,999 --> 00:10:10,000
You've never once seen me

117
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,378
as a servant.

118
00:10:13,391 --> 00:10:14,977
You've never disdained me.

119
00:10:16,548 --> 00:10:17,549
Therefore,

120
00:10:20,697 --> 00:10:24,057
I don't care what the future holds,

121
00:10:30,117 --> 00:10:31,817
I will be your Phob

122
00:10:32,495 --> 00:10:35,177
forever and ever.

123
00:10:44,496 --> 00:10:45,976
Now you're saying nice things to me.

124
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:49,786
But I will study in the UK in two months.

125
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:53,697
By then you might be happy

126
00:10:54,207 --> 00:10:56,617
that you don't have to
follow me around anymore.

127
00:10:59,732 --> 00:11:00,817
- Your Highness.
- Phob.

128
00:11:06,777 --> 00:11:08,497
- Stop it!
- Stay away.

129
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:10,577
- Your Highness!
- Come here.

130
00:11:13,703 --> 00:11:16,097
My dad scolded me because of you,
you stupid servant!

131
00:11:16,513 --> 00:11:18,937
He sent you to school
so you could serve me.

132
00:11:19,037 --> 00:11:20,337
Instead, you chose to be a star.

133
00:11:20,614 --> 00:11:23,737
You didn't know your place,
you're just dust under my feet.

134
00:11:24,159 --> 00:11:26,417
You hear me! Get out!

135
00:11:36,281 --> 00:11:37,457
You stupid servant!

136
00:11:38,057 --> 00:11:41,257
You hurt me? I'm going to kill you.

137
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:43,737
What is going on? What is this?

138
00:11:43,836 --> 00:11:45,937
- What?
- Grandma!

139
00:11:45,953 --> 00:11:48,657
He hurt me! Look at this! He hurt me!

140
00:11:48,721 --> 00:11:50,017
He hurt me!

141
00:11:50,039 --> 00:11:52,017
How did you raise him to be like this?

142
00:11:52,257 --> 00:11:54,977
I'm hurt! This is so painful.

143
00:11:55,159 --> 00:11:56,160
Grandma!

144
00:11:56,617 --> 00:11:59,618
Look at me! Why don't you look at me now?

145
00:12:00,071 --> 00:12:02,072
You have to look at me!

146
00:12:12,211 --> 00:12:15,617
Prince Wasin and Princess
Pattamapreeya were kind to you

147
00:12:15,895 --> 00:12:18,437
and I still need to punish
you so you will remember this.

148
00:12:20,572 --> 00:12:24,417
But Prince Chatthorn
hurt Prince Tinnakorn first.

149
00:12:24,987 --> 00:12:27,137
I just protected my prince.

150
00:12:28,817 --> 00:12:29,857
Prince Chatthorn

151
00:12:30,377 --> 00:12:32,337
started the whole thing.

152
00:12:34,748 --> 00:12:36,577
Are you talking back to me?

153
00:12:36,791 --> 00:12:39,697
Why don't you know your place?
We're just servants.

154
00:12:39,911 --> 00:12:41,697
Why did you become so full of yourself?

155
00:12:42,732 --> 00:12:43,977
Your grandma

156
00:12:44,247 --> 00:12:46,097
was a servant in the palace.

157
00:12:46,617 --> 00:12:48,737
And I was born here.

158
00:12:49,527 --> 00:12:51,897
We can live like this

159
00:12:51,987 --> 00:12:53,817
because our masters are so kind to us.

160
00:12:53,937 --> 00:12:56,137
But there is no more slavery.

161
00:12:56,837 --> 00:12:58,457
I am grateful for them.

162
00:12:58,887 --> 00:13:01,737
But what he did was
wrong and it was different.

163
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:05,177
You wanted me to be
responsible for what I didn't do?

164
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:08,657
Only the masters can do no wrong?

165
00:13:09,447 --> 00:13:10,448
Phob!

166
00:13:11,969 --> 00:13:14,537
You can't say that or
you will go straight to hell.

167
00:13:15,057 --> 00:13:17,617
He is the master so he can't be guilty.

168
00:13:17,995 --> 00:13:20,937
We are the servants and
we need to accept that.

169
00:13:24,774 --> 00:13:26,417
You need to promise me

170
00:13:26,457 --> 00:13:28,417
that you won't do
something like this ever again.

171
00:13:28,692 --> 00:13:31,897
You need to praise him far above
our own heads, your hear me?

172
00:13:48,337 --> 00:13:50,497
My dad scolded me because
of you, you stupid servant!

173
00:13:50,924 --> 00:13:53,497
He sent you to school
so you could serve me.

174
00:13:53,537 --> 00:13:54,937
Instead, you chose to be a star.

175
00:13:55,697 --> 00:13:58,177
He is the master so he can't be guilty.

176
00:13:58,495 --> 00:14:01,437
We are the servants and
we need to accept that.

177
00:14:16,337 --> 00:14:17,338
Sir?

178
00:14:26,177 --> 00:14:27,178
Sir?

179
00:14:29,337 --> 00:14:31,497
I heard from Euam that
your mom flogged you.

180
00:14:32,425 --> 00:14:33,426
I'm worried about you.

181
00:14:36,487 --> 00:14:37,497
I'm fine.

182
00:14:41,577 --> 00:14:42,681
But…

183
00:14:44,569 --> 00:14:45,737
You have a wound?

184
00:14:46,137 --> 00:14:48,897
It's just this and it's far
from my heart. I'm fine.

185
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:51,577
It's big.

186
00:14:52,417 --> 00:14:53,617
I'm totally fine.

187
00:14:56,079 --> 00:14:57,639
If you don't believe me, just touch it.

188
00:15:00,932 --> 00:15:03,337
See? I'm fine.

189
00:15:24,321 --> 00:15:25,322
Ow!

190
00:15:32,732 --> 00:15:33,733
I…

191
00:15:34,937 --> 00:15:37,417
Are you hurt? I'm sorry.

192
00:15:40,769 --> 00:15:41,770
I'm just teasing you.

193
00:15:42,857 --> 00:15:43,858
Come on.

194
00:15:44,377 --> 00:15:45,378
This is fun.

195
00:15:49,769 --> 00:15:52,217
I brought some salve to put on your wounds.

196
00:15:55,337 --> 00:15:56,338
I…

197
00:15:57,135 --> 00:15:58,495
Come on, let me put it on for you.

198
00:15:58,937 --> 00:16:00,617
I…wait.

199
00:16:01,492 --> 00:16:02,493
I can put it on myself.

200
00:16:02,521 --> 00:16:03,937
I can do it for you.

201
00:16:04,831 --> 00:16:06,057
It's okay, Your Highness.

202
00:16:06,697 --> 00:16:08,337
- I can do it.
- Phob!

203
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,053
Don't move.

204
00:16:13,852 --> 00:16:14,853
I'll take off your top.

205
00:16:27,897 --> 00:16:28,898
It stings a little.

206
00:16:30,381 --> 00:16:31,782
I can put it on for you.

207
00:16:42,455 --> 00:16:43,456
It will sting a little.

208
00:16:58,780 --> 00:16:59,781
Does it hurt?

209
00:17:01,377 --> 00:17:02,617
I can take it.

210
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:18,829
Does it hurt here?

211
00:18:06,492 --> 00:18:07,493
Phob, honey.

212
00:18:22,804 --> 00:18:23,805
What did you say?

213
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,377
You want me to punish your son?

214
00:18:27,777 --> 00:18:30,097
Yes, Your Highness. He was guilty

215
00:18:30,806 --> 00:18:31,977
for hurting the master.

216
00:18:34,609 --> 00:18:38,017
Nual, it's water under the bridge.

217
00:18:38,177 --> 00:18:41,297
Why are you bringing it up?

218
00:18:41,508 --> 00:18:44,897
Also, Phob didn't mean to hurt him.

219
00:18:45,737 --> 00:18:48,737
But my son was really guilty.

220
00:18:49,687 --> 00:18:51,137
He didn't know his place.

221
00:18:51,831 --> 00:18:53,337
And he became this way

222
00:18:53,932 --> 00:18:55,257
because he was arrogant.

223
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:58,457
He thought that he's
Prince Tinnakorn's favorite.

224
00:18:59,574 --> 00:19:02,817
I think you should refrain him

225
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:05,097
from taking care of Prince Tinnakorn.

226
00:19:05,457 --> 00:19:07,237
So he'd stop acting like this.

227
00:19:07,468 --> 00:19:09,337
They grew up together

228
00:19:10,417 --> 00:19:13,257
and your son always helps my son.

229
00:19:14,104 --> 00:19:16,153
We should let him do his job.

230
00:19:16,177 --> 00:19:16,857
But…

231
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:20,057
You want us to be cruel masters

232
00:19:20,587 --> 00:19:23,097
who bullied the servants?

233
00:19:42,081 --> 00:19:43,082
Mom!

234
00:19:44,303 --> 00:19:45,304
Mom!

235
00:19:46,257 --> 00:19:47,258
Mom!

236
00:19:48,727 --> 00:19:52,217
Why did you ask Prince Vasin
that I should stop taking care of his son?

237
00:19:52,487 --> 00:19:53,537
Did you eavesdrop earlier?

238
00:19:55,404 --> 00:19:56,457
I did't mean to hear it.

239
00:19:57,257 --> 00:19:59,337
You're getting too close to him.

240
00:20:00,297 --> 00:20:01,497
He is a prince.

241
00:20:01,620 --> 00:20:04,177
- And you're just a servant.
- If he wasn't a prince,

242
00:20:04,297 --> 00:20:05,617
if he had no title,

243
00:20:05,822 --> 00:20:08,657
if we were equal, only then
could we get close to each other?

244
00:20:08,724 --> 00:20:10,037
Shut up.

245
00:20:10,628 --> 00:20:12,017
You will go to hell for this.

246
00:20:12,463 --> 00:20:14,237
Don't say the impossible.

247
00:20:15,177 --> 00:20:16,577
You're a servant

248
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,657
and you should know your place.

249
00:20:19,817 --> 00:20:20,857
From now on,

250
00:20:21,452 --> 00:20:24,097
you can't get any closer
to Prince Tinnakorn, okay?

251
00:20:25,137 --> 00:20:26,837
I'm sorry, Mom.

252
00:20:27,737 --> 00:20:29,777
As long as he needs me close,

253
00:20:30,057 --> 00:20:31,577
I will stay with him like this.

254
00:20:35,497 --> 00:20:36,498
Fine.

255
00:20:37,409 --> 00:20:39,657
He will study abroad soon.

256
00:20:40,177 --> 00:20:43,337
When it happens, even if
he doesn't tell you to go,

257
00:20:43,921 --> 00:20:45,857
you can't follow him there anymore.

258
00:21:03,607 --> 00:21:06,257
My dad came back from
his business trip to France

259
00:21:06,385 --> 00:21:08,257
so he told me to give you this.

260
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:11,337
You're so kind, honey.

261
00:21:11,596 --> 00:21:14,257
- Make yourself at home.
- Yes, ma'am.

262
00:21:24,607 --> 00:21:26,417
The westerners

263
00:21:26,437 --> 00:21:29,377
make such a remarkable perfume.

264
00:21:29,823 --> 00:21:32,977
A beautiful gift from beautiful lady.

265
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:35,017
But the recipient…

266
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:37,577
is even more beautiful.

267
00:21:39,119 --> 00:21:41,780
Look at you,

268
00:21:41,892 --> 00:21:43,913
you've always made jokes
right in front of the guests

269
00:21:43,937 --> 00:21:47,537
since you were young until now.

270
00:21:50,417 --> 00:21:52,297
Siri, don't go home just yet.

271
00:21:52,681 --> 00:21:54,897
You should wait to meet Tinnakorn.

272
00:21:55,396 --> 00:21:58,337
Tinnakorn and Phob should be back soon.

273
00:21:58,577 --> 00:22:00,137
You should wait to meet him.

274
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:04,177
That's right, you should stay.

275
00:22:04,711 --> 00:22:07,217
Would you like to walk in the garden with me?

276
00:22:08,503 --> 00:22:09,857
The roses have just bloomed.

277
00:22:10,593 --> 00:22:11,594
So pretty.

278
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:16,907
Chatthorn, if you're free, then
you should to back to study.

279
00:22:17,697 --> 00:22:19,257
I met your teachers,

280
00:22:19,473 --> 00:22:21,497
and they said that your
grades weren't very good.

281
00:22:22,017 --> 00:22:23,018
But I...

282
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:49,777
Siri? When did you get here?

283
00:23:03,159 --> 00:23:06,457
Saranrom Club will organize a
music event next week.

284
00:23:06,951 --> 00:23:09,757
I heard that there are bands from
overseas, do you want to come?

285
00:23:10,871 --> 00:23:12,657
Do you normally go to the music events?

286
00:23:13,217 --> 00:23:14,919
I shall go, if it is my father’s command.

287
00:23:16,163 --> 00:23:19,456
If my father so commands,
I suppose I shall go.

288
00:23:20,377 --> 00:23:22,097
Why is it up to your dad?

289
00:23:22,721 --> 00:23:24,617
If you want to, you can ask him.

290
00:23:25,399 --> 00:23:27,657
My dad doesn't let me go anywhere.

291
00:23:29,159 --> 00:23:32,198
I only can go places
when he tells me to.

292
00:23:34,903 --> 00:23:36,417
What about this?

293
00:23:37,244 --> 00:23:39,617
If you want to go, I can ask him for you.

294
00:23:41,897 --> 00:23:43,977
You can meet with your
friends and join the society.

295
00:23:44,729 --> 00:23:46,377
- Sounds good?
- Yeah.

296
00:23:47,297 --> 00:23:49,577
In the next few days,

297
00:23:50,017 --> 00:23:51,977
the Thai Red Cross
will organize a big fair.

298
00:23:52,260 --> 00:23:53,897
I think you should visit the fair.

299
00:23:54,431 --> 00:23:56,208
I went there last year
and it was so much fun.

300
00:23:56,232 --> 00:23:57,233
Right, Phob?

301
00:24:01,628 --> 00:24:02,629
Yes, sir.

302
00:24:03,615 --> 00:24:04,616
Let's eat.

303
00:24:10,697 --> 00:24:11,698
Dad?

304
00:24:12,274 --> 00:24:15,037
Why did you stop me
from hanging out with Siri?

305
00:24:15,273 --> 00:24:17,017
Instead, you let Tin hang out with her.

306
00:24:17,727 --> 00:24:19,097
When did you get close to her?

307
00:24:19,828 --> 00:24:22,377
Tinnakorn is closer to Siri than you are.

308
00:24:23,044 --> 00:24:25,257
You will make them feel awkward.

309
00:24:25,772 --> 00:24:27,587
How could it be awkward?

310
00:24:28,148 --> 00:24:31,837
It is obvious that I like her.

311
00:24:32,938 --> 00:24:35,617
I don't like her as a sister

312
00:24:36,308 --> 00:24:38,817
but I see her as a woman.

313
00:24:40,575 --> 00:24:41,787
And I think that

314
00:24:42,930 --> 00:24:44,330
Siri likes me too.

315
00:24:46,812 --> 00:24:48,417
I will talk to you frankly

316
00:24:48,865 --> 00:24:50,497
so you will stop with this nonsense.

317
00:24:51,356 --> 00:24:54,377
Siri's dad and I made an agreement

318
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:56,337
for Tinnakorn to be engaged to Siri.

319
00:24:57,937 --> 00:24:58,938
What?

320
00:25:00,337 --> 00:25:02,857
Why would you do that?

321
00:25:03,247 --> 00:25:06,377
You know well that I like Siri,
why didn't you let me?

322
00:25:06,495 --> 00:25:08,577
Because I don't want to be mortified.

323
00:25:10,132 --> 00:25:11,577
Look at you.

324
00:25:12,017 --> 00:25:14,857
You're doing so bad in school
and you are not a decent human being.

325
00:25:15,188 --> 00:25:19,377
The whole city knows about
you getting into fights with people.

326
00:25:19,913 --> 00:25:22,457
What kind of parents would want you to
marry their daughters?

327
00:25:29,857 --> 00:25:31,577
This is not fair.

328
00:25:35,737 --> 00:25:38,177
You've never given me anything good.

329
00:25:39,857 --> 00:25:42,537
You've always given Tin something good.

330
00:25:42,572 --> 00:25:45,937
- England and Siri. What about me?
- Chatthorn!

331
00:25:47,609 --> 00:25:49,857
Stop thinking about your love life already

332
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:51,737
and focus on your studies.

333
00:25:53,432 --> 00:25:55,897
And don't compare yourself to your brother,

334
00:25:56,387 --> 00:25:58,337
you can't even compare yourself to Phob.

335
00:26:13,353 --> 00:26:15,217
Go back to study.

336
00:26:23,865 --> 00:26:24,866
Phob!

337
00:26:25,775 --> 00:26:26,817
Why are you here?

338
00:26:28,521 --> 00:26:30,497
Princess Siri is gone?

339
00:26:30,737 --> 00:26:33,137
Yeah, I just sent her off.

340
00:26:34,943 --> 00:26:35,944
I see.

341
00:26:36,847 --> 00:26:39,497
So now you have time for me.

342
00:26:41,481 --> 00:26:43,937
What is wrong with you? Phob?

343
00:26:45,844 --> 00:26:46,977
Are you sick?

344
00:26:54,815 --> 00:26:56,737
I saw you enjoying yourself talking to her.

345
00:26:58,633 --> 00:26:59,857
Do you like her?

346
00:27:04,801 --> 00:27:06,411
I feel bad for her.

347
00:27:07,647 --> 00:27:10,977
She needs to follow her dad's orders,
she can't do anything on her own.

348
00:27:11,535 --> 00:27:13,937
I adore her...

349
00:27:18,324 --> 00:27:19,857
but as a sister.

350
00:27:30,647 --> 00:27:32,097
So what is wrong with you?

351
00:27:33,257 --> 00:27:35,897
What's with the grumpy face?

352
00:27:40,487 --> 00:27:43,377
Tin! Are you happy now?

353
00:27:45,697 --> 00:27:48,257
Move, you filthy servant!

354
00:27:51,777 --> 00:27:55,017
Both of you must be laughing at me, right?

355
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:57,567
You know well that I like Siri.

356
00:27:57,641 --> 00:27:59,059
What are you talking about?

357
00:28:00,868 --> 00:28:02,297
Why did you bring Siri into this?

358
00:28:05,676 --> 00:28:07,097
Stop acting so innocent already.

359
00:28:08,607 --> 00:28:10,437
Dad wants you to be engaged to Siri.

360
00:28:12,708 --> 00:28:13,709
What?

361
00:28:25,137 --> 00:28:26,497
What he said is true.

362
00:28:27,269 --> 00:28:28,450
What is your problem?

363
00:28:30,097 --> 00:28:31,098
I…

364
00:28:32,001 --> 00:28:33,857
I don't love her like that.

365
00:28:36,412 --> 00:28:38,377
We're like brother and sister.

366
00:28:40,740 --> 00:28:42,657
It's not always about love.

367
00:28:43,637 --> 00:28:45,137
It's about suitability.

368
00:28:47,663 --> 00:28:50,857
- But I don't love Ruethaisiri.
- Or you love someone else?

369
00:28:58,111 --> 00:28:59,337
Who's the girl?

370
00:29:02,388 --> 00:29:03,389
It's okay.

371
00:29:05,567 --> 00:29:07,817
I don't care who she is.

372
00:29:09,079 --> 00:29:12,057
You can just marry
Ruethaisiri as your first wife.

373
00:29:12,857 --> 00:29:15,497
So she can help take care of the palace.

374
00:29:17,377 --> 00:29:18,817
You're a great man,

375
00:29:19,596 --> 00:29:21,497
you can have 4-5 wives

376
00:29:21,737 --> 00:29:23,417
and I think you can take care of them all.

377
00:29:41,388 --> 00:29:42,537
Soon,

378
00:29:42,764 --> 00:29:45,217
our palace will hear good news

379
00:29:45,265 --> 00:29:47,145
from Prince Tinnakorn
and Princess Ruethaisiri.

380
00:29:48,172 --> 00:29:49,377
You knew about this?

381
00:29:49,907 --> 00:29:52,137
Prince Chat yelled so loud like that,

382
00:29:52,252 --> 00:29:53,497
everyone heard about it.

383
00:29:58,967 --> 00:30:01,377
But Prince Tin doesn't love her like that.

384
00:30:02,271 --> 00:30:04,272
He just adores her as a sister.

385
00:30:06,404 --> 00:30:09,657
His relationship is none of your business.

386
00:30:13,548 --> 00:30:14,857
He is a master,

387
00:30:15,319 --> 00:30:17,257
servants like us can't be involved.

388
00:30:18,007 --> 00:30:19,727
But he shouldn't be forced to be into this.

389
00:30:21,057 --> 00:30:22,058
He should be the one

390
00:30:22,793 --> 00:30:24,857
who decides on his relationship.

391
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:30,737
That's none of your business.

392
00:30:32,737 --> 00:30:33,897
He is a master

393
00:30:34,780 --> 00:30:36,337
and he has his duties to fulfill.

394
00:30:37,628 --> 00:30:39,097
Our duties

395
00:30:40,097 --> 00:30:42,657
are to take care of him and to be grateful.

396
00:30:43,245 --> 00:30:44,250
Don't you see?

397
00:30:45,540 --> 00:30:47,060
This is me trying to give back to him.

398
00:30:47,652 --> 00:30:50,897
I want to help him and make him happy.

399
00:30:51,737 --> 00:30:53,737
I don't want him to marry
someone he doesn't love.

400
00:30:55,487 --> 00:30:56,577
Are you sure about that?

401
00:31:04,468 --> 00:31:07,217
You're not thinking of him as
more than just a master, are you?

402
00:31:15,305 --> 00:31:17,057
- Mom! I..
- Listen to me carefully.

403
00:31:20,638 --> 00:31:22,337
No matter what your thoughts are,

404
00:31:24,134 --> 00:31:25,537
they have to stop now.

405
00:31:27,591 --> 00:31:29,497
Don't drag him to your level.

406
00:31:30,297 --> 00:31:31,498
He is a master

407
00:31:32,113 --> 00:31:33,437
and we are only servants.

408
00:31:34,151 --> 00:31:38,377
We can only respect him as
one of the royal family members.

409
00:31:43,408 --> 00:31:44,409
If one day,

410
00:31:44,697 --> 00:31:46,817
you think of him more
than a master and servant,

411
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:48,697
you will be the one

412
00:31:49,937 --> 00:31:51,577
who will taint his reputation.

413
00:32:53,055 --> 00:32:56,097
♪ A mischievious ♪

414
00:32:58,457 --> 00:33:02,782
♪ and hard-working ♪

415
00:33:05,716 --> 00:33:08,177
♪ man named Ngoh ♪

416
00:33:12,788 --> 00:33:18,497
♪ He saw a daughter ♪

417
00:33:25,537 --> 00:33:28,257
♪ of a ruler. ♪

418
00:33:32,945 --> 00:33:38,097
♪ Her skin is glowing ♪

419
00:33:43,495 --> 00:33:48,057
♪ like the moon. ♪

420
00:34:34,980 --> 00:34:38,817
Prince Yai's live performance is so great.

421
00:34:41,729 --> 00:34:45,072
His group is the most popular in the city.

422
00:34:46,193 --> 00:34:48,857
My grandma has booked the group for months.

423
00:34:58,271 --> 00:34:59,272
Scoot over.

424
00:35:01,273 --> 00:35:02,274
Move your leg.

425
00:35:03,540 --> 00:35:04,541
Move your leg.

426
00:35:04,817 --> 00:35:05,837
One leg at a time.

427
00:35:06,031 --> 00:35:08,457
- Move my leg?
- Follow me. Watch me.

428
00:35:09,620 --> 00:35:12,937
One at a time like this, follow my lead.

429
00:35:13,777 --> 00:35:15,778
Now speed up! Speed up!

430
00:35:17,756 --> 00:35:18,757
Look at me!

431
00:35:20,377 --> 00:35:22,017
- Do you know what it is?
- What?

432
00:35:26,257 --> 00:35:27,258
Like Ngoh!

433
00:35:29,975 --> 00:35:30,976
Smile.

434
00:35:33,716 --> 00:35:35,956
You saw me as an ugly and
dirty-looking guy, didn't you?

435
00:35:36,889 --> 00:35:37,977
If that's the case,

436
00:35:38,767 --> 00:35:39,857
from now on,

437
00:35:40,649 --> 00:35:42,617
I won't help you study anymore.

438
00:35:43,262 --> 00:35:44,857
Stop sulking already.

439
00:35:46,654 --> 00:35:49,857
I mean you look like Ngoh
when he shows his real self.

440
00:36:02,281 --> 00:36:04,977
Ngoh's skin is covered with gold.

441
00:36:08,169 --> 00:36:09,337
But I'm just a servant,

442
00:36:10,878 --> 00:36:12,177
I am nothing like him.

443
00:36:16,657 --> 00:36:20,657
Nobody would toss me a
garland like she did to him.

444
00:36:39,777 --> 00:36:40,778
It's no garland,

445
00:36:45,777 --> 00:36:47,617
but you can have this cotton rose.

446
00:37:04,193 --> 00:37:05,577
Does this mean that

447
00:37:08,721 --> 00:37:12,057
you tossed me the garland?

448
00:37:22,217 --> 00:37:23,337
Is that right?

449
00:37:44,393 --> 00:37:46,257
I'm hungry.

450
00:37:47,417 --> 00:37:49,817
Let's find something to eat in the kitchen.

451
00:38:08,462 --> 00:38:10,337
Don't drag him to your level.

452
00:38:11,217 --> 00:38:12,377
He is a master

453
00:38:12,937 --> 00:38:14,257
and we are only servants.

454
00:38:15,097 --> 00:38:19,177
We can only respect him as
one of the royal family members.

455
00:38:21,415 --> 00:38:22,416
If one day,

456
00:38:22,570 --> 00:38:24,530
you think of him more
than a master and servant,

457
00:38:24,898 --> 00:38:27,930
you will be the one who
will taint his reputation.

458
00:38:59,836 --> 00:39:00,837
Nual.

459
00:39:01,114 --> 00:39:03,410
Where is Phob? It's
about time to go to school.

460
00:39:04,012 --> 00:39:06,937
Well, he left early this morning.

461
00:39:07,052 --> 00:39:08,837
He said that he'd study before class first.

462
00:39:09,177 --> 00:39:11,337
What? He normally waits for me.

463
00:39:11,638 --> 00:39:12,777
Why did he leave first?

464
00:39:13,617 --> 00:39:15,097
I don't know, Your Highness.

465
00:39:15,761 --> 00:39:17,537
But it is better this way.

466
00:39:18,145 --> 00:39:20,737
He is a servant, you should
let him go to school by himself.

467
00:39:30,817 --> 00:39:32,497
[Royal Pages School]

468
00:39:43,225 --> 00:39:44,226
Kamol?

469
00:39:45,196 --> 00:39:46,577
Have you seen Phobthee?

470
00:39:46,637 --> 00:39:49,657
I haven't. He's normally
around you all the time.

471
00:39:51,193 --> 00:39:52,937
Let's go, we don't want to be late.

472
00:39:53,177 --> 00:39:54,178
- Let's go.
- Come on.

473
00:40:17,372 --> 00:40:18,817
I want to play soccer next week.

474
00:40:19,054 --> 00:40:20,177
Sure, you want to join?

475
00:40:20,353 --> 00:40:21,433
- Sure.
- You're joining us?

476
00:40:21,479 --> 00:40:24,017
- We need Weerapon to join the team.
- He needs to come.

477
00:40:24,119 --> 00:40:26,857
He's so good at blocking.

478
00:40:26,999 --> 00:40:28,297
- So great.
- Phob.

479
00:40:30,127 --> 00:40:31,128
There you are.

480
00:40:31,977 --> 00:40:33,697
Let's get back home.
The driver is waiting.

481
00:40:39,505 --> 00:40:40,657
I have to run some errands.

482
00:40:42,724 --> 00:40:44,044
I think I will go home by myself.

483
00:40:46,577 --> 00:40:48,097
You can go home, Your Highness.

484
00:40:56,340 --> 00:40:57,340
What's wrong?

485
00:40:58,777 --> 00:40:59,857
I'm not mad at you.

486
00:41:02,388 --> 00:41:03,457
I'm just a servant.

487
00:41:04,017 --> 00:41:06,897
- How could I be mad at the master?
- Enough with the master and servant.

488
00:41:09,657 --> 00:41:10,982
I know!

489
00:41:11,529 --> 00:41:14,097
You're still thinking about
Chat's insults, don't you?

490
00:41:16,017 --> 00:41:17,737
It has nothing to do with him.

491
00:41:18,497 --> 00:41:19,777
Then what is it about?

492
00:41:24,009 --> 00:41:25,010
I..

493
00:41:25,759 --> 00:41:27,897
Have I offended you?

494
00:41:30,415 --> 00:41:32,097
Can you tell me?

495
00:41:33,137 --> 00:41:36,017
I could have done something
and I didn't know it, so tell me.

496
00:41:37,857 --> 00:41:39,297
If I know, I won't do it again.

497
00:41:41,009 --> 00:41:43,337
But you refuse to tell me anything.

498
00:41:44,977 --> 00:41:47,177
I don't know what to do.

499
00:41:52,852 --> 00:41:54,783
Phob! Phob!

500
00:41:56,708 --> 00:42:00,185
Hey, what is the name of the female vendor
in front of the school?

501
00:42:01,257 --> 00:42:02,937
The one that you helped her the other day.

502
00:42:04,748 --> 00:42:08,097
(In unison) Saijai.

503
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:11,057
Here, she wanted me
to give you some snacks.

504
00:42:12,233 --> 00:42:13,577
You're quite something.

505
00:42:14,191 --> 00:42:16,337
That Saijai who is pretty
with nice skin, right?

506
00:42:16,697 --> 00:42:18,817
Whoa! Aren't you a charmer?

507
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:20,511
Our friend is quite something, isn't he?

508
00:42:21,217 --> 00:42:24,337
Hey! There is a new bar at Charoen Krung.

509
00:42:24,452 --> 00:42:25,497
Should we give it a try?

510
00:42:25,617 --> 00:42:27,497
- Let's go.
- I'll buy Phob some drinks.

511
00:42:27,988 --> 00:42:30,337
He tutored us until we passed the test.

512
00:42:32,799 --> 00:42:34,817
- You should come, Your Highness.
- Please come.

513
00:42:40,309 --> 00:42:41,337
Come on. Let's go.

514
00:42:41,719 --> 00:42:43,257
Don't be late.

515
00:42:51,057 --> 00:42:52,658
I think you should go home first.

516
00:43:02,175 --> 00:43:04,176
Cheers!

517
00:43:14,273 --> 00:43:15,697
You shouldn't be drinking too much.

518
00:43:18,396 --> 00:43:20,356
We're at the bar so we
need to drink some liquor.

519
00:43:21,097 --> 00:43:22,817
You expected me to have some desserts?

520
00:43:24,337 --> 00:43:26,737
That's right. Having
some desserts? Cheers!

521
00:43:29,017 --> 00:43:32,057
You're right, Your Highness.

522
00:43:32,415 --> 00:43:34,737
We're not at Saijai's
stall selling desserts.

523
00:43:39,017 --> 00:43:41,777
Among all of us, I think Phob

524
00:43:41,881 --> 00:43:43,507
will be the first with a girlfriend.

525
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:46,437
Of course, Saiji has such beautiful eyes.

526
00:43:46,581 --> 00:43:47,977
And she flirted with you.

527
00:43:48,215 --> 00:43:51,537
As a real man, you should reciprocate.

528
00:43:52,737 --> 00:43:53,818
Shut up!

529
00:44:16,689 --> 00:44:19,577
Hey! I lost the bet and I
still need to buy you drinks?

530
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:22,817
You can have another
round to make it up next time.

531
00:44:27,892 --> 00:44:29,932
I told you that you shouldn't
be drinking too much.

532
00:44:34,057 --> 00:44:35,217
Did you watch me?

533
00:44:37,329 --> 00:44:38,377
How could you ask me that?

534
00:44:40,033 --> 00:44:41,617
You should know it well that

535
00:44:42,716 --> 00:44:45,297
I care for you every day.

536
00:44:46,364 --> 00:44:48,097
Well, that was before.

537
00:44:50,513 --> 00:44:53,577
Now you could care more about that Saijai.

538
00:44:54,273 --> 00:44:55,274
Your Highness.

539
00:44:55,737 --> 00:44:57,537
You should care for her.

540
00:44:58,837 --> 00:45:02,097
And you can forget what you said about...

541
00:45:04,037 --> 00:45:05,038
being my Phob.

542
00:45:19,365 --> 00:45:20,777
Enough with your sarcasm already.

543
00:45:23,817 --> 00:45:25,297
You should know well that

544
00:45:25,967 --> 00:45:29,257
I meant what I said.

545
00:45:30,964 --> 00:45:33,377
I will be your loyal servant,

546
00:45:34,137 --> 00:45:35,338
always have and always will.

547
00:45:36,084 --> 00:45:37,217
Why did you avoid me?

548
00:45:38,879 --> 00:45:42,577
You've been avoiding
me all day. What did I do?

549
00:45:45,077 --> 00:45:46,577
It's not your fault.

550
00:45:46,900 --> 00:45:49,017
So you accepted the fact
that you avoided seeing me.

551
00:45:50,089 --> 00:45:51,857
Why didn't you tell me?

552
00:45:54,207 --> 00:45:56,517
We've talked about
everything since we were young.

553
00:45:56,697 --> 00:45:59,657
Did you know that you hurt my feeling
when you acted like that?

554
00:46:01,588 --> 00:46:02,589
You know?

555
00:46:05,329 --> 00:46:06,330
Something

556
00:46:07,362 --> 00:46:08,577
can't be said.

557
00:46:09,580 --> 00:46:10,937
Because I'm worried that

558
00:46:11,911 --> 00:46:13,537
you wouldn't understand

559
00:46:14,652 --> 00:46:16,177
and you could hate me.

560
00:46:20,188 --> 00:46:21,337
Just try to say it.

561
00:46:26,055 --> 00:46:27,056
Actually…

562
00:46:32,497 --> 00:46:33,498
I..

563
00:46:35,361 --> 00:46:36,362
I…

564
00:46:47,241 --> 00:46:48,857
I think we should go home

565
00:46:50,437 --> 00:46:51,697
so you can rest.

566
00:47:16,326 --> 00:47:18,127
You should have let me fall.

567
00:47:20,129 --> 00:47:22,337
So I'll get used to it
when you're not around.

568
00:47:22,967 --> 00:47:23,968
Your Highness,

569
00:47:25,223 --> 00:47:27,743
it's not like I wanted to give you
the cold shoulder or ignore you.

570
00:47:29,097 --> 00:47:31,897
I was just worried that if I said it,

571
00:47:32,337 --> 00:47:33,577
you would hate me.

572
00:47:36,409 --> 00:47:37,857
Why don't you try to say it?

573
00:47:39,502 --> 00:47:42,577
I promise you that no
matter what you say or do,

574
00:47:42,637 --> 00:47:43,957
I will not hate or be mad at you.

575
00:47:46,177 --> 00:47:47,178
I promise.

576
00:48:26,337 --> 00:48:28,577
Who are they?
What are they doing in the back?

577
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:43,000
(Next Episode)

578
00:48:47,100 --> 00:48:51,100
I saw what you two were doing
behind the bar that night.

579
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:53,900
There you are, Your Highness.

580
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:59,500
Just now, I saw Phob and Tin
heading towards the servants' quarters.

581
00:49:00,100 --> 00:49:04,700
No matter what, I want to be
Your Highness's Phob... forever.

